           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000">
                      <font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> <a href="http://www.gamespy.com/interviews/june03/eqldonpc/" target="_blank">http://www.gamespy.com/interviews/june03/eqldonpc/</a><br /><br />I found this interesting.  Perhaps it's just a case of Shawn Lord not providing a lengthy enough answer, but does this mean that groups of 4 or less or solo play are not possible?<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">GameSpy: What are the party size constraints of entering a dynamic dungeon? <br /><br />Shawn Lord: Parties of five or six characters will be able to travel the Lost Dungeons.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Later...<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">GameSpy: Do players have an equal chance of getting cool new stuff? <br /><br />Shawn Lord: Everyone that buys the expansion will have access to the dungeons and will be able to get new items.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Everyone will have access as long as they are in a group of 5 or 6?  <br /><br />I can't imagine that they would require that the only possible way to enjoy the entire expansion is to have a group of 5-6 people, but seeing how the whole concept of raiding seems to be going out the window with this one, I'm just wondering if they may just go totally hardcore and eliminate small groups and soloers as well.  Doesn't seem smart, but you never know. <br /><br />Thoughts?<br /><br /><br /></span id="msg"></font>
