                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Vague, but vague for a reason, because probably a lot of this stuff is far from being completed and is probably still in conceptual stages.  I think what he was saying was that the expansion is designed to accomodate small groups, meaning that the 'adventures' were tuned to be encounters that are reasonably accomplishable by a small group of 5-6 people.  <br /><br />I don't think that they would REQUIRE 5-6.  If you want to attempt the adventure solo, then you ought to be able to do that; it just might not turn out too well.  However, from my reading of that article it sounded like the content of the adventures is dynamic to the strength/weakness of the group attempting it.  Did anyone else get that impression?  If that's the case, maybe a soloer could venture in and not be confronted with more than he can realistically handle, if he plays skillfully.  That would be pretty cool.<br /><br />I think their heart is in the right place anyway.  Focusing on something besides raid quality content is something that the game has needed for awhile; but it's going to be hard to balance that risk with a reward decent enough to draw people away from raids without turning the encounters into farm-quests.  If they can pull that off, I'll say they've hit a home-run.<br /><br />I'm looking forward to this one for some reason...I just have a good feeling about the content.  Of course, I love dungeons, so the idea sells itself to me.  Hopefully I won't be disappointed.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td valign="bottom"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=545380" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.angelfire.com/vamp/bfreeland/vhampyre-signature.jpg" border="0"></a></span></font></td>
