                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> LDoN is going to support Zone instancing.  This means me and my group talk to the NPC and he tells us where to go.  We go and zone in.  The server creates a dungeon instance that you and your group only are teleported into the dungeon.  Another group can be working against the same dungeon, but in a different dungeon instance.  <br /><br />Some of the things I find interesting is talking about the dungeons being somewhat based on the level of your raiding party.  How in the world are they going to tell the strength of your party?  Level only?  I hope not.  We could have 2 groups, both with the same makeup and all members be lvl 65.  Based on armor, weaps, spells, AA's, those 2 groups could have entirely different ability levels.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
