                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">What kind of loot can they award from a 90min 1 group encounter? Stuff that is better than everything in Luclin outside of VT?<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />I predict that they're going to create two new additional slots to be filled.  They're going to call them the POCKET slots.  In order to utilize any item in these slots, you must be wearing something in your LEG slot.  They will all be NO DROP so you must buy the new expansion in order to get one of these new POCKET items.  <br /><br />On a serious note though, they don't have to create loot that is better than VT.  VT is a raid level zone.  You can't (I don't think?) go in to Vex Thall with a single group and get raid level VT gear.<br /><br />I don't think they'll be tailoring this expansion to the raiding guilds at all.  All they have to do is make the loot better than other single groupable types of loot.  At a guess, that probably means items with 40 to 75 HP/Mana instead of 60 to 100 hp/mana.  This is pure guess though.<br /><br />Better than Thurg/SS (which is all single groupable), but less than VT.<br /><br />Those of us that have raid level toons won't be getting gear upgrades out of these zones I bet.  I'm hardly a raiding necro (only sitting at just over 2khp), so I may be able to find the odd upgrade here.  But the Yag's of the world aren't likely to find much here.<br /><br />Alts could though, or you could go there for friends who may not be as well equipped.  It also sounds like they're going to implement tiered quests of some sort....ala level 1,2,3,4,5,6,7 levels or Item X.  Level 7 usually takes forever and has decent stats (prayer shawls, ring wars...etc..only better).</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td