                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I don't think the question of loot is as important as the question of experience.  If they can design these encounters so that they grant experience that is comparable to your standard experience grinding group in the planes, then these dungeons should be a big hit.  The reason that the LoY expansion did not draw the mid-to-high 50's people out of the planes was not because the loot was poor, but because the experience gain relative to mob difficulty is much worse than in the planes.  People sit in the planes for hours killing the same trash mobs over and over with no real expectation of loot, because it the easiest way to advance their characters.<br /><br />This game does not need more zones for farmers to draw loot from, it needs more places where small groups of friends/guildies can level their characters in a fun and imaginative way.  Hopefully, this is what the new expansion will focus on.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
