                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> And what exactly happens if that five person group loses someone to LD or that person has to go? They get kicked out of the dungeon? And if they don't get kicked out, why can't I just get four twinks and create an instance for 40 other people with just those four twinks? Or are they going to not let you gate out either? <br /><br />Instancing isn't as good an idea as some people like to think.  It's great for raid encounters and events, but poor for general dungeon crawls.  And by forcing people to go in groups of 5-6, even with the exp bonus, SOE is just going to have more people sitting on their butts with the lfg flag on each night since you won't even be able to two-box, duo, or work with small groups anymore.<br /><br />Artificial constraints are almost always bad.  Just take a look at PoP's maximum-capped encounters.  But a max-cap simply means you have to min/max your group a bit more, which, though it leaves certain classes in the dust (e.g. PoJ trials), doesn't prevent you from doing more with less.  A min-cap means you *have* to bring a bunch of people, even if it's overkill to do so, and that just creates problems.<br /><br />I guess we'll have to see the exact implementation before any solid dsicussions can be made, but in general I am wary of any and all artificial constraints because they tend to limit play style and force people to play in a way they do not want to play in.<br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td valign="bottom"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Etadanik the Redeemed</span></font></td>
                    </tr>
